	<config>
		<documentation>System requirements:
The Control4® Dock for iPod requires system software 1.7.1 or later.

Network connectivity:
The Dock is controlled, and cover art is shared over a 10/100 BaseT Ethernet connection and can be configured with both DHCP and Static IP options.  ZigBee is NOT available.  A Static IP address can be set through System Manager.

Reset network settings:
The process to reset the Dock to DHCP is to depress the ID button while plugging the Dock into Power.  After the LED flashes white (1 to 2 seconds) the Dock will be configuration to DHCP.  Power cycle the Dock again so that it will reboot and request a DHCP address.

Supported iPods:
The Control4 Dock is designed to work with late generation iPods that support Apple’s iPod Accessory Protocol (iAP).  At the time of release the Dock and this driver have been tested to work with the following iPods and the latest Apple firmware release as listed below:

iPod touch (1st and 2nd generation with Apple software Version 2.2.1)
iPod nano (1st, 2nd, 3rd and 4th generation with Apple software Version 1.1.3)
iPod classic (80GB, 120GB, 160GB with Apple software Version 2.0.1)
iPod (5th generation (video) with Apple software Version 1.3)
iPhone and iPhone 3G with Apple software Version 2.2.1

iPod software:
For best results we recommend that customers keep their iPod software updated to the latest version released from Apple.  For most iPods the software version can been viewed on the iPod under Settings\About\Version.  iPod software can be updated through iTunes which can be downloaded at http://www.apple.com/itunes/download/.

LED:
The Dock has a single multi-color LED on the front of the unit.  The LED status states are as follows and may be useful during troubleshooting:

LED - Network status:
When no iPod is present in the Dock the normal LED states are as follows:

WHITE/off flashing – initial boot

RED solid – Offline without IP address or retrieving IP address

YELLOW solid – Online with IP address (but not connected to C4 controller)

GREEN flashing (2 flashes) – identifying to controller (identify button has been pushed)

GREEN solid – Ready (Dock has IP address, connected to controller, no iPod in the Dock)

PURPLE flashing – updating firmware

LED - iPod status:
Without good network connectivity the iPod will not play in the Control4 environment, therefore, Network status takes precedence.  If the dock has booted properly, and has the proper connectivity to the network and controller then the following LED status applies.  Otherwise the LED status listed above should apply even if an iPod is docked.

BLUE/YELLOW flashing - Connecting iPod

BLUE solid - iPod Connected/Ready

BLUEGREEN solid - media is streaming from the iPod (the iPod is playing music or video through the Dock).


Driver Properties

Cover Art:
Music and Video cover art can be displayed on the iPod “Now Playing” page of Control4 Navigators.  While the iPod is sending the cover art to the Navigator screen the iPod’s transport controls (Play, Pause, FF, RW, etc) are not available.  Because of this we allow the installer to set when, or even if, cover art is sent to and displayed on the Navigators.  Under the Properties page you can select the following:
Off:  No cover art will be displayed on the Navigators.  Transport controls for the iPod should be available most any time during music or video playback.
Delay xx seconds:  Indicates how soon after the song begins cover art will be requested from the iPod.  While the iPod transfers the cover art transport controls will be unavailable.   The amount of time it takes for cover art to be transferred can vary from just a few seconds to up to ten seconds depending on the size of the cover art and the iPod. NOTE: Retrieving cover art may cause some iPods to lockup during playback.
During the first song of a Playlist the Control4 system will request the cover art for the first song, wait several seconds and then request the cover art for the next song.  The default setting is to delay 10 seconds.
Disable: Disable cover art support. This removes the ability for the user to turn off cover art or set a delay. The "Cover Art" button is removed from the UI.

Now Playing Timer:
This setting allows the dealer to adjust whether or not the Now Playing page displays the time stamp for the current playing song (how many minutes and seconds have elapsed and remain in the current song).  The dealer can also set how often this information is updated on the Now Playing page -- the default is every three seconds.

Room Off:
This setting allows the dealer to set the command that is sent to the iPod when a Room Off command is selected.  The default (recommended) command is Stop but the dealer can also chose Pause.

Debug Mode:
When enabled this setting allows the dealer to capture traces for the Dock.

Firmware version:
The firmware version of the Dock is listed on the Properties page.  The version information is updated when an iPod is docked.  As new Dock firmware is available it will be updated as part of the system software update process like other Control4 products.

		</documentation>
		<identify_text>Press the identify button located on the bottom of the Control4 Dock for iPod, or Type the network address below.</identify_text>
		<properties>
			<property>
				<name>Cover Art</name>
				<type>LIST</type>
				<items>
					<item>Off</item>
					<item>Delay 0 Seconds</item>
					<item>Delay 5 Seconds</item>
					<item>Delay 10 Seconds</item>
					<item>Delay 15 Seconds</item>
					<item>Delay 30 Seconds</item>
					<item>Disable</item>
				</items>
				<default>Disable</default>
				<readonly>false</readonly>
			</property>
			<property>
				<name>Now Playing Timer</name>
				<type>LIST</type>
				<items>
					<item>Off</item>
					<item>On</item>
					<item>Every 2 Seconds</item>
					<item>Every 3 Seconds</item>
					<item>Every 5 Seconds</item>
				</items>
				<default>Every 3 Seconds</default>
				<readonly>false</readonly>
			</property>
			<property>
				<name>Room Off</name>
				<type>LIST</type>
				<items>
					<item>Stop iPod</item>
					<item>Pause iPod</item>
				</items>
				<default>Stop</default>
				<readonly>false</readonly>
			</property>
			<property>
				<name>Alpha Lookup</name>
				<type>LIST</type>
				<items>
					<item>Enabled</item>
					<item>Disabled</item>
				</items>
				<default>Disabled</default>
				<readonly>false</readonly>
			</property>
			<property>
				<name>Debug Mode</name>
				<type>LIST</type>
				<items>
					<item>Off</item>
					<item>Print</item>
					<item>Log</item>
					<item>Print and Log</item>
				</items>
				<default>Off</default>
				<readonly>false</readonly>
			</property>
			<property>
				<name>Firmware Version</name>
				<type>STRING</type>
				<default></default>
				<readonly>true</readonly>
			</property>
		</properties>
		<actions>
			<action>
				<name>Display Globals</name>
				<command>DisplayGlobals</command>
			</action>
		</actions>
		<commands>
			<command>
				<name>Set LED</name>
				<description>Set NAME LED Mode to PARAM1</description>
				<params>
					<param>
						<name>Setting</name>
						<type>LIST</type>
						<items>
							<item>On</item>
							<item>Off</item>
						</items>
					</param>
				</params>
			</command>
		</commands>
		<script>
	<![CDATA[
proxyBinding = 5001

function forceDebugOn()
	g_debugprint = true; g_debuglog = true; g_debugunittest = true;
end

----------------------------------------- property handling -----------------------------------------
function OnPropertyChanged(strProperty)
	if (strProperty == "Debug Mode") then
		if (Properties[strProperty] == "Off") then
			g_debugprint = false
			g_debugunittest = false
			g_debuglog = false
			g_DebugTimer = 0
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Print") then
			g_debugprint = true
			g_debugunittest = false
			g_debuglog = false
			startDebugTimer()
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Log") then
			g_debugprint = false
			g_debugunittest = true
			g_debuglog = true
			startDebugTimer()
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Print and Log") then
			g_debugprint = true
			g_debugunittest = true
			g_debuglog = true
			startDebugTimer()
		end
	end

	if (strProperty == "Alpha Lookup") then
		if (Properties[strProperty] == "Disabled") then
			gAlphaLookup = false
		else
			gAlphaLookup = true
		end
	end

	if (strProperty == "Cover Art") then
		g_SupportCoverArt = true
		local numseconds = string.match(Properties[strProperty],  "Delay (%d+).+")
		
		if (Properties[strProperty] == "Off") then
			g_ShowCoverArt = false
		elseif (numseconds == "0") then
			g_CoverArtDelay = 1
			g_ShowCoverArt = true
		elseif (numseconds == "5") then
			g_CoverArtDelay = 5
			g_ShowCoverArt = true
		elseif (numseconds == "10") then
			g_CoverArtDelay = 10
			g_ShowCoverArt = true
		elseif (numseconds == "15") then
			g_CoverArtDelay = 15
			g_ShowCoverArt = true
		elseif (numseconds == "30") then
			g_CoverArtDelay = 30
			g_ShowCoverArt = true
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Disable") then
			g_ShowCoverArt = false
			g_SupportCoverArt = false
		end

		SendUISimpleToProxy("showcoverart", tostring(g_ShowCoverArt))
		SendUISimpleToProxy("coverartsupport", tostring(g_SupportCoverArt))
	end

	if (strProperty == "Now Playing Timer") then
		if (Properties[strProperty] == "Off") then
			g_NowPlayingTimer = false
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "On") then
			g_NowPlayingDelay = 1
			g_NowPlayingTimer = true
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Every 2 Seconds") then
			g_NowPlayingDelay = 2
			g_NowPlayingTimer = true
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Every 3 Seconds") then
			g_NowPlayingDelay = 3
			g_NowPlayingTimer = true
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Every 5 Seconds") then
			g_NowPlayingDelay = 5
			g_NowPlayingTimer = true
		end
		ClearElapsedTime()
	end

	if (strProperty == "Room Off") then
		if (Properties[strProperty] == "Stop iPod") then
			g_RoomOffCommand = "STOP_RAW"
		elseif (Properties[strProperty] == "Pause iPod") then
			g_RoomOffCommand = "PAUSE_RAW"
		end
	end

	if (Properties[strProperty] == "Firmware Version") then
		C4:UpdateProperty("Firmware Version", g_firmwareVersion)
	end
end


function startDebugTimer()
	if (g_DebugTimer) then
		g_DebugTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_DebugTimer)
	end
	g_DebugTimer = C4:AddTimer(45, "MINUTES")
end


function dbg(strDebugText)
	if (g_debugprint) then print (strDebugText) end
	if (g_debuglog) then C4:ErrorLog("c4iPodDock: " .. strDebugText) end
end


function dbgUnitTest(strDebugText)
	if (g_debugunittest) then print (strDebugText) end
	if (g_debuglog) then C4:ErrorLog("c4iPodDock: " .. strDebugText) end
end


function dbgFunction(strFunction)
	local debugFunction = true
	if (g_debugprint and debugFunction) then print ("Function:\t" .. strFunction .. ":") end
	if (g_debuglog  and debugFunction) then C4:ErrorLog("c4iPodDock: " .. strFunction) end
end


function dbgParams(tParams)
	if ((g_debugprint or g_debuglog) and tParams ~=nil) then
		if (type(tParams) == "string") then
			dbg("   " .. tostring(tParams))
		else
			for k,v in pairs(tParams) do
				dbg("   " .. tostring(k) .. ":  " .. tostring(v))
			end
		end
	end
end


function dbgValue(name, value)
	dbg(tostring(name) .. " = " .. tostring(value))
end


function EscapeXML(strEscaped)
	local temp = C4:XmlEscapeString(strEscaped)
	return temp
end

function startCoverArtTimer()
	if (g_CoverArtTimer) then
		g_CoverArtTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_CoverArtTimer)
	end
	if (g_ShowCoverArt == true) then
		g_CoverArtTimer = C4:AddTimer(g_CoverArtDelay, "SECONDS")
	end
end

function startSelectItemTimer()
	if (g_SelectTimer) then
		g_SelectTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_SelectTimer)
	end
	g_SelectTimer = C4:AddTimer(500, "MILLISECONDS")
end

function startDockedTimer()
	if (g_DockedTimer) then
		g_DockedTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_DockedTimer)
	end
	g_DockedTimer = C4:AddTimer(500, "MILLISECONDS")
end

function OnTimerExpired(idTimer)
	if (idTimer == g_DebugTimer) then
		dbg("Turning Debug Mode Off (timer expired)")
		C4:UpdateProperty("Debug Mode", "Off")
	elseif (idTimer == g_CoverArtTimer) then
		dbg("CoverArtTimer expired")
		GetCoverArt()
	elseif (idTimer == g_SelectTimer) then
		dbg("SelectItemTimer expired")
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["SELECT_RAW"], 0, g_SelectItemId, 0, 0, "")
	elseif (idTimer == g_DockedTimer) then
		dbg("DockedTimer expired")
		GetNext(1, 20)
		CMD.GET_REPEAT()
		CMD.GET_SHUFFLE()
		CMD.GET_FIRMWARE_VERSION("")
	end
	C4:KillTimer(idTimer)
end

-- Release things this driver had allocated...
function OnDriverDestroyed()
	-- Kill open timers
	if (g_DebugTimer ~= nil) then g_DebugTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_DebugTimer) end
	if (g_CoverArtTimer ~= nil) then g_CoverArtTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_CoverArtTimer) end
	if (g_SelectTimer ~= nil) then g_SelectTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_SelectTimer) end
	if (g_DockedTimer ~= nil) then g_DockedTimer = C4:KillTimer(g_DockedTimer) end
end

--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-  iPod Dock-Specific Code -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

CMD = {
	GET_LIST_RAW 		= 0x01,
	SELECT_RAW 			= 0x02,
	PLAYITEM_RAW 		= 0x03,
	BACK_RAW 			= 0x04,
	ALPHA_RAW 			= 0x05,
	GET_COVERART_RAW 	= 0x06,
	RESET_DB_SELECTION = 0x07,
	GET_IPORT_NAME 	= 0x08,
	GET_SHUFFLE_MODE_RAW 	= 0x09,
	GET_REPEAT_MODE_RAW = 0x0A,
	GET_NOW_PLAYING_RAW 	= 0x0B,

	PLAYPAUSE           = 0x21,
	PLAY_RAW            = 0x22,
	PAUSE_RAW           = 0x23,
	STOP_RAW            = 0x24,
	SKIP_REV_RAW        = 0x25,
	SKIP_FWD_RAW        = 0x26,
	START_SCAN_FWD_RAW  = 0x27,
	STOP_SCAN_FWD_RAW   = 0x28,
	START_SCAN_REV_RAW  = 0x29,
	STOP_SCAN_REV_RAW   = 0x2A,
	SET_SHUFFLE_RAW     = 0x2B,
	SET_REPEAT_RAW      = 0x2C,
	SET_VIDEO_OUTPUT_RAW = 0x2D,
	GET_FW_VERSION_RAW  = 0x2E,
	SET_LED_RAW         = 0x2F,
}

RESP = {
	LIST 					= 0x81,
	LIST_ITEM 			= 0x82,
	ALPHA_LOOKUP 		= 0x85,
	COVER_ART 			= 0x86,
	SHUFFLE_MODE 		= 0x87,
	REPEAT_MODE 		= 0x88,
	FW_VERSION   		= 0xAE,
}

NOTIFY = {
	IPOD_NAME 			= 0x91,
	NOW_PLAYING 		= 0x92,
	TIME 		 			= 0x93,
	PLAYER_STATUS 		= 0x94,
	DOCK_STATUS 		= 0x95,
}

----------- Additional Proxy Commands ---------------

function CMD.SCAN_FWD(tParams)
	SendSimpleDockCmd(CMD["START_SCAN_FWD_RAW"])
	SendSimpleDockCmd(CMD["STOP_SCAN_FWD_RAW"])
end


function CMD.SCAN_REV(tParams)
	SendSimpleDockCmd(CMD["START_SCAN_REV_RAW"])
	SendSimpleDockCmd(CMD["STOP_SCAN_REV_RAW"])
end


function CMD.GET_ELAPSED_TIME(tParams)
		if (g_NowPlayingTimer == true) then
			SendElapsedTimeUI()
		else
			ClearElapsedTime()
		end
end


function CMD.GET_PROGRESS(tParams)
	SendToProxy("PROGRESS", {current = g_current, total = g_totalsongs})
end


function CMD.REQUEST_CURRENT_MEDIA_INFO(tParams)
	NotifyRoomOfCurrentMedia()
end


function CMD.QUERY_CURRENT_SETTINGS(tParams)
	if (g_online == true) then
		SendUISimpleToProxy("online", "true")
	else
		SendUISimpleToProxy("online", "false")
	end

	NotifyRoomOfCurrentMedia()
	if (g_NowPlayingTimer == true) then
		SendElapsedTimeUI()
	else
		ClearElapsedTime()
	end
	SendProgressUI()

	SendUISimpleToProxy("iportname", g_ipodname)
	SendUISimpleToProxy("playstatus", g_playerstatus)
	SendUISimpleToProxy("showcoverart", tostring(g_ShowCoverArt))
	SendUISimpleToProxy("coverartsupport", tostring(g_SupportCoverArt))
	SendUISimpleToProxy("alphalookup", tostring(gAlphaLookup))
	CMD.GET_REPEAT()
	CMD.GET_SHUFFLE()
	if ((g_ListType == LISTTYPE.MUSIC) or (g_ListType == "0")) then
		CMD.GET_LIST()
	end
	CMD.GET_FIRMWARE_VERSION("")

	SendUISimpleToProxy("shufflemode", g_shuffle[g_shufflemode])
	SendUISimpleToProxy("repeatmode", g_repeat[g_repeatmode])
end

function CMD.SELECT_TOP_MUSIC_ITEM(tParams)
	if (g_ListType ~= LISTTYPE.MUSIC) then
		g_ListType = LISTTYPE.MUSIC
		SendToProxy("UPDATE_LIST_TYPE", {listtype = g_ListType})
	end
	ResetDock()
	g_SelectItemId = tParams["ITEM_ID"]
	startSelectItemTimer()
end

function CMD.SELECT_TOP_VIDEO_ITEM(tParams)
	if (g_ListType ~= LISTTYPE.VIDEO) then
		g_ListType = LISTTYPE.VIDEO
		SendToProxy("UPDATE_LIST_TYPE", {listtype = g_ListType})
	end
	ResetDock()
	g_SelectItemId = tParams["ITEM_ID"]
	startSelectItemTimer()
end

function CMD.SELECT_TOP_INDEX(tParams)
	if (tParams["RESET_DOCK"] == "1") then
		ResetDock()
		g_SelectItemId = tParams["ITEM_ID"]
		startSelectItemTimer()
	else
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["SELECT_RAW"], 0, tParams["ITEM_ID"], 0, 0, "")
	end
end

function CMD.GET_ALPHA_LOOKUP(tParams)
	dbg ("CMD.GET_ALPHA_LOOKUP")
	if (gAlphaLookup) then
		dbgValue("LETTER", tParams["LETTER"])
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["ALPHA_RAW"], string.byte(tParams["LETTER"]), 0, 0, 0, "")
	else
		dbg("ALPHA_LOOKUP disabled")
	end
end

function CMD.GET_REPEAT(tParams)
	QueueSimpleDockCmd(CMD["GET_REPEAT_MODE_RAW"])
end

function ToggleRepeat()
	g_repeatmode = g_repeatmode + 1
	if (g_repeatmode > 3) then
		g_repeatmode = 1
	end
end

function CMD.SET_REPEAT(tParams)
	if (tParams == nil) then
		ToggleRepeat()
	else
		local repeatMode = tParams["REPEAT_MODE"]
		if (repeatMode == nil) then
			ToggleRepeat()
		else
			g_repeatmode = tonumber(repeatMode) + 1
		end
	end
	QueueDockCmd(CMD["SET_REPEAT_RAW"], g_repeatmode, 0, 0, 0, "")
	SendUISimpleToProxy("repeatmode", g_repeat[g_repeatmode])
end


function CMD.TOGGLE_COVERART(tParams)
	if (g_gettingCoverArt == true) then
		dbg ("Getting Cover Art: Skipping TOGGLE_COVERART command")
	elseif (g_SupportCoverArt == false) then
		dbg ("Cover Art not supported on this device or is disabled.")
	else
		SetGettingCoverArt(false)
		if (g_ShowCoverArt == true) then
			dbg ("Turning off cover art")
			g_imagequeue = {}
			C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Off")
		else
			dbg ("Turning on cover art")
			if (g_CoverArtDelay == 1) then
				C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Delay 0 Seconds")
			elseif (g_CoverArtDelay == 5) then
				C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Delay 5 Seconds")
			elseif (g_CoverArtDelay == 10) then
				C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Delay 10 Seconds")
			elseif (g_CoverArtDelay == 15) then
				C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Delay 15 Seconds")
			elseif (g_CoverArtDelay == 30) then
				C4:UpdateProperty("Cover Art", "Delay 30 Seconds")
			end
			g_imagequeue = {}
		end
		OnPropertyChanged("Cover Art")
		SendUISimpleToProxy("showcoverart", tostring(g_ShowCoverArt))

		g_imageindex = g_current
		GetCoverArt()
	end
end


function CMD.GET_SHUFFLE(tParams)
	QueueSimpleDockCmd(CMD["GET_SHUFFLE_MODE_RAW"])
end

function ToggleShuffle()
	g_shufflemode = g_shufflemode + 1
	if (g_shufflemode > 3) then
		g_shufflemode = 1
	end
end

function CMD.SET_SHUFFLE(tParams)
	if (tParams == nil) then
		ToggleShuffle()
	else
		local shuffleMode = tParams["SHUFFLE_MODE"]
		if (shuffleMode == nil) then
			ToggleShuffle()
		else
			g_shufflemode = tonumber(shuffleMode) + 1
		end
	end
	g_imagequeue = {}
	QueueDockCmd(CMD["SET_SHUFFLE_RAW"], g_shufflemode, 0, 0, 0, "")
	SendUISimpleToProxy("shufflemode", g_shuffle[g_shufflemode])
end


function CMD.SET_VIDEO_OUT(tParams)
	local videoType = tonumber(tParams["OUTPUT_TYPE"])
	dbgFunction("CMD.SET_VIDEO_OUT(" .. VIDEOTYPE[videoType] .. ")")

	if (g_videoType ~= videoType) then
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["SET_VIDEO_OUTPUT_RAW"], videoType, 0, 0, 0, "")
	end
end

function CMD.GET_FIRMWARE_VERSION(tParams)
	QueueSimpleDockCmd(CMD["GET_FW_VERSION_RAW"])
end

function CMD.LIST_SELECT(tParams)
	if (tParams == nil) then
		return
	end

	for k,v in pairs(tParams) do dbg(k .. ":  " .. v) end

	local item = tonumber(tParams["ITEM"])
	local itemtype = tonumber(tParams["TYPE"])
	local itemtitle = tParams["TITLE"]
	if (itemtitle ~= nil) then
		itemtitle = itemtitle .. tohex("0")
	else
		itemtitle = ""	-- Must have a title.
	end

	-- if item selected is music or video (starts playing music or video)
	if ((itemtype == 1) or (itemtype == 2)) then
		g_imagequeue = {}
		SendUISimpleToProxy("page", "NowPlaying")
	end

	-- Navigator sends -501 on selecting a list item out of boundaries...
	-- Don't allow invalid select, or selecting an item while inside a selection...
	if (item == -501) then
		return
	end

	-- NO SELECT = 32006
	if (item == 32006) then
		return
	end

	-- Toggle Cover Art = 32008
	if (item == 32008) then
		CMD.TOGGLE_COVERART()
		g_selectedItem = 11
		GetNext(1, 20)
		return
	end

	-- Don't select invalid items
	if (item < 0) then
		return
	end

	-- START OVER = 32004
	if (item == 32004) then
		dbg("START OVER")
		ResetDock()
--    g_stack:cleartable()
		return
	end

	-- Shuffle = 32002
	if (item == 32002) then
		CMD.SET_SHUFFLE()
		g_selectedItem = 9
		GetNext(1, 20)
		return
	end

	-- Repeat = 32001
	if (item == 32001) then
		CMD.SET_REPEAT()
		g_selectedItem = 10
		GetNext(1, 20)
		return
	end

	-- BACK = 32003
	if (item == 32003) then
		g_selectedItem = g_stack:pop()
		QueueSimpleDockCmd(CMD["BACK_RAW"])
		return
	else
		-- Regular Select...  item ID in param1...
		if ((itemtype == nil) or (itemtype > 2)) then
			g_stack:push(item)
		end
		if (g_hasAll == true) then
			item = item - 1
		end
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["SELECT_RAW"], 0, item, 0, 0, itemtitle)
	end
end

function CMD.RESET(tParams)
	if (nil ~= tParams) then
		for k,v in pairs(tParams) do dbg(k .. ":  " .. v) end
		local listType = tParams["TYPE"]
		if (g_ListType ~= listType) then
			g_ListType = tParams["TYPE"]
			SendToProxy("UPDATE_LIST_TYPE", {listtype = g_ListType})
		end
		if ((g_supportsVideo == false) and (listType == "1")) then
			return
		end
	end
	dbg("ResetDock: CMD.RESET")
	ResetDock()
end

function CMD.ALPHA_LOOKUP(tParams)
	dbg ("CMD.ALPHA_LOOKUP")
	if (gAlphaLookup) then
		for k,v in pairs(tParams) do dbg(k .. ":  " .. v) end
		QueueDockCmd(CMD["ALPHA_RAW"], string.byte(tParams["LETTER"]), 0, 0, 0, "")
	else
		dbg("ALPHA_LOOKUP disabled")
	end
end

function CMD.LIST_BACK(tParams)
